text: David Murphy (born 1985) is a Gaelic footballer from County Laois. He plays at wing forward for Laois and in 2003 was part of the Laois team that won the All-Ireland Minor Football Championship title for the first time since 1997. He scored a late equaliser in the drawn final against Dublin to secure a replay. In 2006, Murphy was part of the Laois team that won the Leinster U21 Football Championship. ==References== Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Laois inter-county Gaelic footballers Category:Portarlington Gaelic footballers
